1
00:01:37,150 --> 00:01:40,140
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,170 --> 00:01:43,229
[Episode 24]

3
00:01:43,570 --> 00:01:44,640
Regarding the previous questions

4
00:01:44,640 --> 00:01:46,750
about the nature
of the Mountain Patrol's work,

5
00:01:46,750 --> 00:01:48,550
I need to reflect on my mistakes.

6
00:01:52,090 --> 00:01:53,289
I didn't expect that,

7
00:01:54,759 --> 00:01:55,870
driven by profit,

8
00:01:55,900 --> 00:01:56,450
these people

9
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:57,670
would be so lawless.

10
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:04,130
I owe He an apology.

11
00:02:07,820 --> 00:02:09,419
I didn't look after him well.

12
00:02:13,270 --> 00:02:14,330
There is a pension.

13
00:02:16,290 --> 00:02:17,690
Collect it from Li.

14
00:02:18,530 --> 00:02:19,329
It's not much.

15
00:02:21,370 --> 00:02:23,770
Just a token of the county's appreciation.

16
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:32,810
Nine pairs of cotton shoes.

17
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:35,170
Eleven pairs of gloves.

18
00:02:36,150 --> 00:02:36,870
I think,

19
00:02:37,670 --> 00:02:39,040
there's also a quilt.

20
00:02:40,710 --> 00:02:41,360
Wait.

21
00:02:41,490 --> 00:02:43,150
The numbers don't match here.

22
00:02:44,530 --> 00:02:45,730
Some are crossed out,

23
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:47,010
and some aren't.

24
00:02:49,870 --> 00:02:51,600
What on earth was he recording?

25
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:53,350
It's a mess.

26
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:56,190
Such simple accounts,

27
00:02:56,190 --> 00:02:57,680
yet he could mess them up.

28
00:03:06,410 --> 00:03:07,410
This is the letter

29
00:03:08,570 --> 00:03:10,230
you brought me before he left.

30
00:03:17,340 --> 00:03:18,000
Wangmu,

31
00:03:18,450 --> 00:03:19,300
going into the mountains this time,

32
00:03:19,300 --> 00:03:21,020
I might be gone for a long time.

33
00:03:21,970 --> 00:03:23,760
The debts I owed your shop before,

34
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:25,000
I made a mess of them.

35
00:03:25,810 --> 00:03:27,270
I'll let you in on a secret.

36
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:28,160
Some

37
00:03:28,190 --> 00:03:29,920
were secretly crossed them out

38
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,380
to save the team money.

39
00:03:32,430 --> 00:03:33,020
This is a record

40
00:03:33,020 --> 00:03:34,610
I kept privately.

41
00:03:35,130 --> 00:03:36,980
How much was owed each time,

42
00:03:37,079 --> 00:03:38,610
I've listed it all clearly.

43
00:03:39,030 --> 00:03:40,360
Wait for me to come back.

44
00:03:40,510 --> 00:03:42,310
We'll clear this up face to face.

45
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:44,960
Make sure you don't tell

46
00:03:44,960 --> 00:03:46,030
Captain and Bai Ju,

47
00:03:46,650 --> 00:03:48,190
or I'll become a traitor.

48
00:03:50,210 --> 00:03:50,900
Wangmu,

49
00:03:51,470 --> 00:03:52,310
wait for me.

50
00:04:01,710 --> 00:04:02,840
The letter from him,

51
00:04:04,330 --> 00:04:05,010
why is it...

52
00:04:08,340 --> 00:04:09,240
I understand.

53
00:04:11,950 --> 00:04:12,910
Actually,

54
00:04:15,230 --> 00:04:16,760
I understand his feelings.

55
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:21,600
Accounts that can never be cleared.

56
00:04:23,740 --> 00:04:24,390
So that

57
00:04:25,510 --> 00:04:27,240
he could always come back here.

58
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,390
We could always meet again.

59
00:04:36,390 --> 00:04:37,370
But why did he

60
00:04:38,740 --> 00:04:40,159
never dare to say it?

61
00:04:45,159 --> 00:04:46,240
I understand him.

62
00:04:47,700 --> 00:04:48,520
But I also

63
00:04:49,170 --> 00:04:50,530
never dared to say it.

64
00:04:54,460 --> 00:04:55,920
Because we always thought

65
00:04:59,360 --> 00:05:00,820
there would be a next time.

66
00:05:03,060 --> 00:05:03,830
A next time

67
00:05:05,270 --> 00:05:06,270
to meet again.

68
00:05:09,050 --> 00:05:10,650
According to our tradition,

69
00:05:12,330 --> 00:05:13,390
now that he's gone,

70
00:05:15,070 --> 00:05:16,670
everything belonging to him

71
00:05:19,990 --> 00:05:21,060
should not be kept.

72
00:05:28,730 --> 00:05:29,990
But this account book,

73
00:05:32,370 --> 00:05:33,300
I want to keep it.

74
00:05:36,540 --> 00:05:37,460
What he owes me,

75
00:05:39,540 --> 00:05:40,450
what I owe him.

76
00:05:43,730 --> 00:05:45,130
I want to keep it forever.

77
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:19,890
We're leaving now.

78
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:22,020
Bai Ji's cooking is still the best.

79
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:22,480
I thought,

80
00:06:22,480 --> 00:06:23,810
I'd never get to eat it again.

81
00:06:23,810 --> 00:06:25,340
Then let's come here often.

82
00:06:26,310 --> 00:06:26,810
Yan,

83
00:06:27,270 --> 00:06:27,950
what are you doing?

84
00:06:27,950 --> 00:06:29,600
I said I wouldn't take your money.

85
00:06:29,600 --> 00:06:30,620
You left it on the counter and ran.

86
00:06:30,620 --> 00:06:31,080
Take it.

87
00:06:31,390 --> 00:06:32,810
You're running a business.

88
00:06:32,810 --> 00:06:34,010
If you don't take money,

89
00:06:34,010 --> 00:06:34,480
we'll be too embarrassed

90
00:06:34,480 --> 00:06:35,370
to come back.

91
00:06:35,430 --> 00:06:37,190
You only had three bowls of noodles.

92
00:06:37,190 --> 00:06:38,640
You shouldn't give this much.

93
00:06:38,640 --> 00:06:39,130
Wait.

94
00:06:39,470 --> 00:06:40,640
Let me get you change.

95
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:41,380
No need.

96
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:42,659
Maybe next time.

97
00:06:42,750 --> 00:06:43,860
Hurry go inside
and take care of the customers.

98
00:06:43,860 --> 00:06:44,860
I'm going to work.

99
00:06:47,659 --> 00:06:49,370
Come to my house after work.

100
00:06:49,640 --> 00:06:50,640
My sister sent you

101
00:06:50,659 --> 00:06:52,190
cosmetics from Guangzhou.

102
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:53,900
Got it.

103
00:06:54,020 --> 00:06:55,080
See you after work.

104
00:06:57,540 --> 00:06:58,940
Stop laughing. Let's go.

105
00:07:01,360 --> 00:07:01,930
Here.

106
00:07:01,980 --> 00:07:03,110
Beef with potatoes.

107
00:07:04,300 --> 00:07:04,680
Here.

108
00:07:04,810 --> 00:07:05,310
Han,

109
00:07:05,710 --> 00:07:07,020
don't just take their wine.

110
00:07:07,020 --> 00:07:08,660
Captain, I want to drink this.

111
00:07:08,660 --> 00:07:09,340
It's fine.

112
00:07:09,370 --> 00:07:10,200
Drink whatever you want.

113
00:07:10,200 --> 00:07:10,890
Drink this.

114
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,170
Restaurant Kunlun.

115
00:07:14,300 --> 00:07:14,870
Good.

116
00:07:15,820 --> 00:07:16,580
Mr. Bai,

117
00:07:17,110 --> 00:07:18,130
this name

118
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,540
is a bit too grand.

119
00:07:19,910 --> 00:07:20,500
Is it?

120
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:21,630
Yes, it is.

121
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:23,090
Not really.

122
00:07:26,500 --> 00:07:27,500
County Mayor Duo,

123
00:07:27,810 --> 00:07:28,510
you old comrades

124
00:07:28,510 --> 00:07:29,840
always say that phrase.

125
00:07:30,030 --> 00:07:31,160
How does it go again?

126
00:07:32,820 --> 00:07:34,290
"There will be bread.

127
00:07:34,450 --> 00:07:35,690
There will be milk.

128
00:07:36,130 --> 00:07:37,600
There will be everything."

129
00:07:37,600 --> 00:07:39,060
I believe sooner or later,

130
00:07:39,450 --> 00:07:39,950
it will become

131
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:41,370
a real Restaurant Kunlun.

132
00:07:41,370 --> 00:07:43,570
Then let me congratulate Mr. Bai first.

133
00:07:43,670 --> 00:07:44,730
Congratulations.

134
00:07:45,720 --> 00:07:46,510
Bai Ji,

135
00:07:46,800 --> 00:07:47,830
don't get too excited.

136
00:07:47,830 --> 00:07:49,010
He's not doing it for you.

137
00:07:49,010 --> 00:07:50,080
He's just craving alcohol.

138
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:51,770
He's been thinking about this meal
for days.

139
00:07:51,770 --> 00:07:52,830
Nonsense.

140
00:07:52,850 --> 00:07:53,190
It's fine.

141
00:07:53,190 --> 00:07:54,240
Haven't... Haven't you been thinking too?

142
00:07:54,240 --> 00:07:54,610
It's fine.

143
00:07:54,610 --> 00:07:56,250
Haven't you all been thinking?

144
00:07:56,250 --> 00:07:57,650
Pour it for me. Fill it up.

145
00:08:00,030 --> 00:08:00,420
Ju,

146
00:08:00,510 --> 00:08:01,560
help me take care of them.

147
00:08:01,560 --> 00:08:02,390
I have two more dishes coming right up.

148
00:08:02,390 --> 00:08:03,020
Don't worry.

149
00:08:03,020 --> 00:08:03,880
Go back to work.

150
00:08:10,130 --> 00:08:11,320
Bai Ji is right.

151
00:08:15,160 --> 00:08:16,690
Pastures in the wilderness

152
00:08:17,120 --> 00:08:18,520
can become a county town.

153
00:08:19,330 --> 00:08:22,100
Tattered tents can become a hospital.

154
00:08:22,930 --> 00:08:24,590
Four or five tables and chairs

155
00:08:24,790 --> 00:08:26,190
can become a restaurant.

156
00:08:29,320 --> 00:08:30,450
Our Mountain Patrol

157
00:08:32,100 --> 00:08:33,100
will also witness

158
00:08:33,100 --> 00:08:34,000
Bolamula

159
00:08:35,350 --> 00:08:36,880
becoming a nature reserve.

160
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:51,400
To He Qingyuan.

161
00:08:58,560 --> 00:08:59,830
For Dongzhiba.

162
00:09:00,890 --> 00:09:01,800
For Zhang Yang.

163
00:09:03,870 --> 00:09:05,270
For the Mountain Patrol.

164
00:09:11,650 --> 00:09:12,770
For Bolamula.

165
00:09:29,890 --> 00:09:31,430
Can I add one more?

166
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:32,230
Add what?

167
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:35,080
For permanent positions.

168
00:09:37,030 --> 00:09:39,130
That's all you ever think about.

169
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:40,100
Come on.

170
00:09:40,100 --> 00:09:40,840
For permanent positions. Come on.

171
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:41,180
Come on.

172
00:09:41,180 --> 00:09:42,980
Cheers to permanent positions.

173
00:09:52,110 --> 00:09:53,770
How are you calculating this?

174
00:09:54,940 --> 00:09:56,080
Sixteen plus seven point five,

175
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,280
what does that equal?

176
00:10:01,710 --> 00:10:02,940
The editor-in-chief of our newspaper

177
00:10:02,940 --> 00:10:04,070
contacted me today.

178
00:10:04,870 --> 00:10:06,360
He said the shutting down

179
00:10:06,390 --> 00:10:07,530
of the  Qima'er Gold Mine

180
00:10:07,530 --> 00:10:08,730
has had a huge impact.

181
00:10:09,130 --> 00:10:10,780
Many newspapers have reached out to us,

182
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:12,380
wanting to repost our story.

183
00:10:12,430 --> 00:10:13,660
Some from outside the province,

184
00:10:13,660 --> 00:10:14,990
even some from Beijing.

185
00:10:16,800 --> 00:10:17,400
Captain.

186
00:10:18,170 --> 00:10:18,910
For us,

187
00:10:18,940 --> 00:10:20,270
this is an opportunity.

188
00:10:21,820 --> 00:10:22,880
Are you suggesting

189
00:10:23,240 --> 00:10:24,290
we publish another report?

190
00:10:24,290 --> 00:10:24,890
No.

191
00:10:26,080 --> 00:10:27,330
Repeating myself would make me

192
00:10:27,330 --> 00:10:28,660
look like an amateur.

193
00:10:29,930 --> 00:10:31,120
You kid.

194
00:10:32,110 --> 00:10:32,960
You only seem to be arrogant

195
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:33,800
in front of me.

196
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:35,590
In front of a certain comrade,

197
00:10:35,590 --> 00:10:36,650
you wouldn't dare.

198
00:10:37,390 --> 00:10:38,120
Are you listening or not?

199
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:39,780
Are you going to tell me or not?

200
00:10:40,540 --> 00:10:41,470
I am.

201
00:10:43,500 --> 00:10:45,700
I've prepared a two-pronged approach.

202
00:10:45,790 --> 00:10:46,650
Bring them in,

203
00:10:47,340 --> 00:10:48,740
and send the message out.

204
00:10:49,860 --> 00:10:50,500
Explain.

205
00:10:51,280 --> 00:10:52,010
I think

206
00:10:52,630 --> 00:10:53,790
promoting environmental awareness

207
00:10:53,790 --> 00:10:55,470
needs a long process.

208
00:10:55,960 --> 00:10:56,410
But right now,

209
00:10:56,410 --> 00:10:58,060
as for the importance
of the Mountain Patrol's work,

210
00:10:58,060 --> 00:10:58,990
people who haven't been through it

211
00:10:58,990 --> 00:11:01,080
find it hard to immediately empathize.

212
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:01,940
I want to invite

213
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:02,520
domestic and provincial media

214
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:03,500
who are interested to know more

215
00:11:03,500 --> 00:11:04,300
