00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:39,240
the county has

299
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,390
specifically organized

300
00:13:40,390 --> 00:13:41,960
a focused investigation

301
00:13:42,440 --> 00:13:43,660
targeting the Bolamula region's

302
00:13:43,660 --> 00:13:44,790
illegal mining

303
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:46,900
and poaching activities.

304
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:49,550
Now, let's invite

305
00:13:49,670 --> 00:13:50,510
this operation's

306
00:13:50,510 --> 00:13:51,410
main person in charge,

307
00:13:51,410 --> 00:13:52,410
Comrade Duojie,

308
00:13:52,530 --> 00:13:53,480
to introduce

309
00:13:53,500 --> 00:13:54,760
the specific details.

310
00:14:02,120 --> 00:14:04,180
Before introducing this operation,

311
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:06,790
I'd like to take a moment

312
00:14:07,620 --> 00:14:08,740
to tell you

313
00:14:09,050 --> 00:14:09,830
how our team

314
00:14:09,860 --> 00:14:10,690
came to be.

315
00:14:22,580 --> 00:14:24,110
As early as three years ago,

316
00:14:24,340 --> 00:14:25,460
we realized that

317
00:14:25,710 --> 00:14:28,110
Mazhi, as a major animal husbandry county,

318
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:29,450
will never transform

319
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:30,390
by just staring at the rears

320
00:14:30,390 --> 00:14:31,650
of cows and sheep.

321
00:14:33,300 --> 00:14:34,210
Back then,

322
00:14:34,550 --> 00:14:36,150
County Mayor Lin Lin decided

323
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:37,750
to shift our focus

324
00:14:38,130 --> 00:14:39,620
to resource development,

325
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:40,720
especially

326
00:14:40,820 --> 00:14:42,440
the mineral resources

327
00:14:42,510 --> 00:14:44,440
in the Bolamula Uninhabited Zone.

328
00:14:44,770 --> 00:14:46,100
To benefit Mazhi

329
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:47,430
and help its people

330
00:14:47,770 --> 00:14:49,370
live prosperous lives.

331
00:14:50,790 --> 00:14:53,390
Later, proposed by
the County Party Committee

332
00:14:53,510 --> 00:14:55,110
and decided by city leaders,

333
00:14:55,200 --> 00:14:56,120
we established

334
00:14:56,220 --> 00:14:58,550
the Mazhi Economic Development Company.

335
00:14:59,890 --> 00:15:01,150
We called it a company,

336
00:15:01,430 --> 00:15:02,160
but at first,

337
00:15:02,180 --> 00:15:04,110
there were only eight or nine of us.

338
00:15:04,150 --> 00:15:05,850
Four were even illiterate.

339
00:15:07,300 --> 00:15:08,250
To be honest,

340
00:15:09,700 --> 00:15:10,700
in the beginning,

341
00:15:11,130 --> 00:15:12,190
we didn't consider

342
00:15:12,200 --> 00:15:13,800
environmental protection.

343
00:15:14,310 --> 00:15:16,040
We just focused on the present,

344
00:15:16,630 --> 00:15:18,490
hoping to find mineable deposits

345
00:15:18,680 --> 00:15:20,870
in Bolamula.

346
00:15:22,740 --> 00:15:23,800
But unexpectedly,

347
00:15:24,780 --> 00:15:26,010
my first trip deep into

348
00:15:26,010 --> 00:15:26,850
Bolamula

349
00:15:27,800 --> 00:15:29,390
completely overturned

350
00:15:29,850 --> 00:15:30,990
what I had imagined.

351
00:15:34,920 --> 00:15:36,110
As we drove in,

352
00:15:36,940 --> 00:15:38,940
there were tire tracks everywhere.

353
00:15:39,270 --> 00:15:40,450
They looked like

354
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:42,010
unhealable wounds.

355
00:15:43,370 --> 00:15:44,500
Along the way, we saw

356
00:15:44,740 --> 00:15:45,810
hundreds of

357
00:15:45,840 --> 00:15:47,500
Tibetan antelope skeletons.

358
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:49,710
They had all been skinned,

359
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:51,320
left bloody and mangled.

360
00:15:52,610 --> 00:15:54,230
These silent bones

361
00:15:54,360 --> 00:15:55,400
told me

362
00:15:55,880 --> 00:15:57,060
that in Bolamula,

363
00:15:57,220 --> 00:15:58,570
an endless slaughter

364
00:15:58,890 --> 00:16:00,550
is taking place.

365
00:16:01,050 --> 00:16:01,820
How many people

366
00:16:01,820 --> 00:16:02,750
did you call?

367
00:16:03,360 --> 00:16:04,440
I thought I printed too many,

368
00:16:04,440 --> 00:16:05,410
but we ran out before

369
00:16:05,410 --> 00:16:05,810
half of them got one.

370
00:16:05,810 --> 00:16:06,360
I tell you,

371
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:08,080
I only made four or five calls.

372
00:16:08,690 --> 00:16:10,420
I didn't expect so many people.

373
00:16:11,050 --> 00:16:11,940
It seems everyone

374
00:16:11,940 --> 00:16:12,480
is quite passionate

375
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:13,400
about our environmental cause,

376
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:13,970
right?

377
00:16:15,620 --> 00:16:17,010
Did you count the people?

378
00:16:17,010 --> 00:16:18,070
Go print some more.

379
00:16:20,150 --> 00:16:20,670
There's...

380
00:16:20,670 --> 00:16:21,390
You go count them.

381
00:16:21,390 --> 00:16:22,060
Go on.

382
00:16:23,340 --> 00:16:24,270
No need to count.

383
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,090
Then we don't need to worry

384
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:28,020
about saving paper for the county.

385
00:16:28,080 --> 00:16:29,200
Print as many as possible.

386
00:16:29,200 --> 00:16:30,580
Print as many as you can.

387
00:16:31,080 --> 00:16:32,470
Anyway, when they go back,

388
00:16:32,470 --> 00:16:34,330
they'll help us distribute them.

389
00:16:38,030 --> 00:16:39,290
Easier said than done.

390
00:16:39,430 --> 00:16:40,560
The lady running the photocopier

391
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:41,760
is tough to deal with.

392
00:16:42,220 --> 00:16:42,720
Bai Ju.

393
00:16:47,220 --> 00:16:49,220
Does that lady need a photo for work?

394
00:16:50,390 --> 00:16:50,920
Let's go.

395
00:16:51,240 --> 00:16:52,670
I'll take a couple of shots of her.

396
00:16:52,670 --> 00:16:53,200
Let's go.

397
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:53,960
Will that work?

398
00:16:53,960 --> 00:16:54,820
Of course.

399
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:55,390
It's no trouble at all.

400
00:16:55,390 --> 00:16:55,760
Hurry up then.

401
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:56,560
Hurry! Hurry!

402
00:16:59,010 --> 00:17:00,290
So far,

403
00:17:01,600 --> 00:17:03,020
in protecting Bolamula,

404
00:17:04,109 --> 00:17:04,720
fighting poaching

405
00:17:04,720 --> 00:17:06,240
and illegal mining,

406
00:17:08,609 --> 00:17:09,599
three young men

407
00:17:09,619 --> 00:17:11,280
have sacrificed their lives.

408
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:16,440
As the Captain,

409
00:17:18,220 --> 00:17:19,880
I have failed these children.

410
00:17:22,480 --> 00:17:23,660
Many people may not understand

411
00:17:23,660 --> 00:17:24,550
what we do.

412
00:17:26,460 --> 00:17:27,220
No money,

413
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,160
no permanent positions,

414
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,630
no wages for six months,

415
00:17:33,540 --> 00:17:35,170
failure after failure,

416
00:17:35,190 --> 00:17:36,720
and even risking our lives.

417
00:17:39,910 --> 00:17:41,040
But I firmly believe

418
00:17:43,110 --> 00:17:45,040
that blood will not be shed in vain.

419
00:17:47,410 --> 00:17:48,680
It is precisely those many failures,

420
00:17:48,680 --> 00:17:49,610
added together,

421
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:51,980
that allow me today

422
00:17:51,980 --> 00:17:53,380
to have this opportunity

423
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:55,320
to stand here

424
00:17:56,050 --> 00:17:57,700
and tell you about Bolamula,

425
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:00,130
and through you,

426
00:18:00,270 --> 00:18:01,720
let more people know

427
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,930
about what this land has suffered.

428
00:18:09,660 --> 00:18:10,620
Some things

429
00:18:11,170 --> 00:18:13,300
cannot be finished in one or two tries.

430
00:18:14,660 --> 00:18:16,250
But someone has to be

431
00:18:16,370 --> 00:18:17,590
the first one to do it.

432
00:18:19,810 --> 00:18:20,770
Our Mountain Patrol

433
00:18:20,770 --> 00:18:21,720
is willing to be

434
00:18:21,750 --> 00:18:22,700
that first one.

435
00:18:25,200 --> 00:18:26,200
And in the future,

436
00:18:27,010 --> 00:18:27,850
we will continue

437
00:18:27,850 --> 00:18:29,140
to persevere.

438
00:18:36,030 --> 00:18:36,740
County Mayor!

439
00:18:36,740 --> 00:18:37,520
County Mayor!

440
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:38,960
County Mayor! County Mayor!

441
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:39,720
County Mayor!

442
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:40,290
County Mayor!

443
00:18:40,290 --> 00:18:40,570
County Mayor!

444
00:18:40,570 --> 00:18:41,220
Deputy County Mayor Duo.

445
00:18:41,220 --> 00:18:42,620
Deputy County Mayor Duo.

446
00:18:42,700 --> 00:18:43,850
Hello, Deputy County Mayor Duo.

447
00:18:43,850 --> 00:18:45,070
I would like to ask you,

448
00:18:45,070 --> 00:18:45,790
regarding Bolamula's

449
00:18:45,790 --> 00:18:47,240
conservation work,

450
00:18:47,260 --> 00:18:48,140
what are your

451
00:18:48,170 --> 00:18:49,400
specific plans going forward?

452
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:49,770
I'm sorry,

453
00:18:49,770 --> 00:18:50,970
I'm a little nervous.

454
00:18:55,070 --> 00:18:56,470
To completely eliminate

455
00:18:57,490 --> 00:18:58,140
poaching

456
00:18:58,690 --> 00:19:00,210
and illegal mining,

457
00:19:01,960 --> 00:19:03,180
and to protect

458
00:19:03,550 --> 00:19:04,610
the wildlife

459
00:19:05,400 --> 00:19:06,250
and mineral resources

460
00:19:06,250 --> 00:19:07,530
permanently,

461
00:19:09,640 --> 00:19:11,170
I think the urgent priority

462
00:19:12,770 --> 00:19:13,810
is to promote the establishment

463
00:19:13,810 --> 00:19:15,480
national nature reserve

464
00:19:16,880 --> 00:19:19,210
and set up an ecological protection base.

465
00:19:22,080 --> 00:19:23,140
When that happens,

466
00:19:24,460 --> 00:19:26,060
our Mountain Patrol members

467
00:19:27,370 --> 00:19:29,630
can become the first batch of employees.

468
00:19:30,170 --> 00:19:31,700
They are very experienced,

469
00:19:32,870 --> 00:19:34,470
and they know Bolamula well.

470
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:38,760
For them personally,

471
00:19:41,110 --> 00:19:42,110
their lives can also have

472
00:19:42,110 --> 00:19:43,240
basic security.

473
00:19:50,520 --> 00:19:51,380
Close the door.

474
00:20:01,330 --> 00:20:02,850
The establishment of the nature reserve

475
00:20:02,850 --> 00:20:04,350
hasn't been clarified in the meeting,

476
00:20:04,350 --> 00:20:06,090
nor has Secretary Chen approved it.

477
00:20:06,090 --> 00:20:06,910
How could you,

478
00:20:06,940 --> 00:20:07,660
announce it to the public

479
00:20:07,660 --> 00:20:09,060
at the press conference?

480
00:20:09,700 --> 00:20:11,030
I brought this matter up

481
00:20:11,070 --> 00:20:12,460
to the county long ago.

482
00:20:12,570 --> 00:20:13,180
But the leadership team

483
00:20:13,180 --> 00:20:14,840
hasn't reached a resolution.

484
00:20:20,140 --> 00:20:21,140
Your actions

485
00:20:21,160 --> 00:20:22,210
have already drawn

486
00:20:22,210 --> 00:20:23,520
so much public attention.

487
00:20:23,520 --> 00:20:25,410
We should seize this momentum

488
00:20:25,750 --> 00:20:27,010
to bring in qualified

489
00:20:27,040 --> 00:20:28,770
and capable mining companies.

490
00:20:28,880 --> 00:20:30,180
Once the development zone is on track,

491
00:20:30,180 --> 00:20:31,060
all of

492
00:20:31,090 --> 00:20:31,640
your previous concerns

493
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:33,010
will simply cease to exist.

494
00:20:33,010 --> 00:20:33,770
You do know that

495
00:20:33,770 --> 00:20:34,510
once the nature reserve

496
00:20:34,510 --> 00:20:35,200
is established,

497
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:36,930
it means a complete mining ban.

498
00:20:37,270 --> 00:20:37,870
Isn't that

499
00:20:37,880 --> 00:20:38,910
a waste of

500
00:20:38,940 --> 00:20:39,500
national resources?

501
00:20:39,500 --> 00:20:40,180
Lin.

502
00:20:41,110 --> 00:20:41,630
We've argued about this issue

503
00:20:41,630 --> 00:20:42,870
so many times.

504
00:20:43,480 --> 00:20:44,290
Over the years,

505
00:20:44,290 --> 00:20:45,110
various forms of

506
00:20:45,110 --> 00:20:45,960
poaching and illegal mining

507
00:20:45,960 --> 00:20:47,000
have seriously damaged

508
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,860
Bolamula's ecological balance.

509
00:20:50,380 --> 00:20:52,040
For many areas to recover,

510
00:20:52,790 --> 00:20:54,160
it will take at least decades,

511
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:55,600
or even centuries.

512
00:20:58,900 --> 00:20:59,370
As for gold mines,

513
00:20:59,370 --> 00:21:01,100
they exist elsewhere in China.

514
00:21:01,490 --> 00:21:03,200
But the plateau's rare species

515
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:04,920
can survive only here.

516
00:21:04,950 --> 00:21:06,250
You're being irrational.

517
00:21:06,250 --> 00:21:07,650
I don't want to have

518
00:21:07,680 --> 00:21:10,080
this endless ideological debate with you.

519
00:21:10,200 --> 00:21:11,070
In short,

520
00:21:11,180 --> 00:21:12,590
the establishment of the nature reserve,

521
00:21:12,590 --> 00:21:13,660
without the county

522
00:21:13,740 --> 00:21:14,770
and higher authorities'

523
00:21:14,770 --> 00:21:15,770
final decision,

524
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:17,640
cannot be announced publicly.

525
00:21:18,310 --> 00:21:19,640
Did I make myself clear?

526
00:21:20,460 --> 00:21:20,850
The reporters

527
00:21:20,850 --> 00:21:21,880
are eating in the cafeteria right now.

528
00:21:21,880 --> 00:21:23,300
Go and explain it to them.

529
00:21:23,770 --> 00:21:25,480
Matters regarding the reserve

530
00:21:25,480 --> 00:21:26,090
must absolutely

531
00:21:26,090 --> 00:21:27,550
not appear in the reports.

532
00:21:32,810 --> 00:21:34,270
You're not going, are you?

533
00:21:35,890 --> 00:21:37,150
I knew you wouldn't go.

534
00:21:37,180 --> 00:21:39,310
I'll send the Propaganda Department.

535
00:21:45,660 --> 00:21:46,550
Go to the cafeteria

536
00:21:46,550 --> 00:21:47,420
and tell Director Wang

537
00:21:47,420 --> 00:21:48,150
to come here.

538
00:21:57,460 --> 00:21:58,890
This was finished a few days ago.

539
00:21:58,520 --> 00:22:02,120
[Request for Approval to Establish
the Mazhi Economic Development Zone]

540
00:21:59,730 --> 00:22:01,660
I forgot to give it to you last time.

541
00:22:02,470 --> 00:22:03,470
Take it back and have a read.

542
00:22:03,470 --> 00:22:05,270
We'll discuss it at the meeting.

543
00:22:06,400 --> 00:22:06,940
Okay.

544
00:22:09,230 --> 00:22:10,560
I'll read it carefully.

545
00:22:20,920 --> 00:22:22,010
As for my report,

546
00:22:22,890 --> 00:22:26,170
[Feasibility Report on Establishing
the Bolamula Nature Reserve]

547
00:22:23,030 --> 00:22:24,560
please take a look at it too.

548
00:22:41,920 --> 00:22:43,180
I cooked a lot tonight.

549
00:22:43,230 --> 00:22:44,290
We'll eat in a bit.

550
00:22:44,440 --> 00:22:45,270
Don't bother.

551
00:22:45,380 --> 00:22:46,140
Just make some noodles

552
00:22:46,140 --> 00:22:47,140
for a quick bite.

553
00:22:47,660 --> 00:22:48,460
What's wrong?

554
00:22:49,090 --> 00:22:49,830
I can't eat.

555
00:22:58,570 --> 00:22:59,680
What happened?

556
00:23:00,550 --> 00:23:01,740
I heard there were a lot of journalists

557
00:23:01,740 --> 00:23:02,920
here for interviews today.

558
00:23:02,920 --> 00:23:04,320
Is our county famous now?

559
00:23:05,010 --> 00:23:05,790
Famous?

560
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:07,110
From now on,

561
00:23:07,140 --> 00:23:09,270
life in the county will be even harder.

562
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:16,180
Why do you say that?

563
00:23:18,050 --> 00:23:18,910
That Duojie...

564
00:23:20,690 --> 00:23:22,620
He didn't give me any warning today

565
00:23:22,620 --> 00:23:23,770
and told the reporters

566
00:23:23,770 --> 00:23:24,460
at the meeting

567
00:23:24,460 --> 00:23:25,290
that he wants to establish some

568
00:23:25,290 --> 00:23:26,460
nature reserve.

569
00:23:27,160 --> 00:23:28,140
This person...

570
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:31,610
Then

571
00:23:32,380 --> 00:23:33,770
Are we dropping

572
00:23:34,290 --> 00:23:36,090
the Economic Development Zone?

573
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:42,540
Once some

574
00:23:42,570 --> 00:23:43,810
nature reserve is established,

575
00:23:43,810 --> 00:23:44,370
it means

576
00:23:44,400 --> 00:23:45,680
all the mineral resources inside

577
00:23:45,680 --> 00:23:46,900
can't be touched.

578
00:23:47,790 --> 00:23:49,510
Then how can we build
the Economic Development Zone?

579
00:23:49,510 --> 00:23:50,160
You have no idea

580
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:50,660
how hard it was for me

581
00:23:50,660 --> 00:23:52,000
just to barely

582
00:23:52,030 --> 00:23:52,880
hold those reporters back

583
00:23:52,880 --> 00:23:54,810
this afternoon.

584
00:23:58,290 --> 00:23:59,550
They don't understand at all

585
00:23:59,550 --> 00:24:00,400
what the most critical problem

586
00:24:00,400 --> 00:24:02,280
for the county is right now.

587
00:24:04,160 --> 00:24:05,070
Did

588
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:07,700
Secretary Chen agree to this?

589
00:24:19,340 --> 00:24:20,400
Secretary Chen...

590
00:24:20,890 --> 00:24:21,680
I've noticed recently

591
00:24:21,680 --> 00:24:23,680
his attitude seems to have changed.

592
00:24:25,340 --> 00:24:27,240
He says environmental protection

593
00:24:27,240 --> 00:24:28,370
is like planting trees today

594
00:24:28,370 --> 00:24:30,770
for future generations to enjoy the shade.

595
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:32,110
He told me to

596
00:24:32,130 --> 00:24:33,430
look at the big picture

597
00:24:33,460 --> 00:24:34,660
and help Duojie more.

598
00:24:35,790 --> 00:24:36,960
We talked until we were blue in the face

599
00:24:36,960 --> 00:24:38,420
just to get the subsidies.

600
00:24:39,530 --> 00:24:40,100
And now that we've tackle

601
00:24:40,100 --> 00:24:41,050
what it seems to be

602
00:24:41,050 --> 00:24:42,250
the largest illegal mining gang

603
00:24:42,250 --> 00:24:42,980
in Bolamula,

604
00:24:43,640 --> 00:24:44,810
we can finally

605
00:24:44,830 --> 00:24:46,000
catch our breath.

606
00:24:47,430 --> 00:24:48,960
I will never agree Duojie

607
00:24:50,360 --> 00:24:52,400
to go on like this.

608
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:56,430
Absolutely not.

609
00:25:06,290 --> 00:25:07,220
Back then,

610
00:25:08,010 --> 00:25:08,760
at the Qinghai-Tibet Highway

611
00:25:08,760 --> 00:25:10,420
construction headquarters,

612
00:25:11,110 --> 00:25:11,940
you were working on a

613
00:25:11,940 --> 00:25:13,090
world-class project

614
00:25:13,090 --> 00:25:14,890
that no one had ever done before.

615
00:25:16,550 --> 00:25:18,610
Could it be any harder than back then?

616
00:25:19,580 --> 00:25:20,200
At that time,

617
00:25:20,200 --> 00:25:21,730
you could always find a way.

618
00:25:22,570 --> 00:25:24,070
I'm sure you can now, too.

619
00:25:34,560 --> 00:25:35,170
Yeah.

620
00:25:39,210 --> 00:25:40,600
There must be a way.

621
00:25:43,420 --> 00:25:44,680
Who is it now?

622
00:25:45,440 --> 00:25:46,440
Don't be annoyed.

623
00:25:46,440 --> 00:25:47,430
Feng is coming today.

624
00:25:47,430 --> 00:25:48,280
You two chat.

625
00:25:50,480 --> 00:25:51,330
Sister-in-law.

626
00:25:51,330 --> 00:25:52,150
You're here.

627
00:25:54,180 --> 00:25:55,240
Feng, you're here.

628
00:25:55,460 --> 00:25:55,990
Mrs. Lin,

629
00:25:56,420 --> 00:25:57,920
I'm here to mooch a meal again.

630
00:25:57,920 --> 00:25:59,250
I feel quite bad about it

631
00:25:59,250 --> 00:26:00,420
so I brought a small gift.

632
00:26:00,420 --> 00:26:00,940
Look at you.

633
00:26:00,940 --> 00:26:02,410
You're always so polite.

634
00:26:02,830 --> 00:26:03,520
Come on in.

635
00:26:03,550 --> 00:26:04,210
Lin is home.

636
00:26:16,340 --> 00:26:17,430
[Use local resources to create fortune]

637
00:26:31,380 --> 00:26:33,910
[Economic development is the only way,
make the people prosperous]

638
00:26:44,660 --> 00:26:45,850
Among over a dozen newspapers

639
00:26:45,850 --> 00:26:46,990
from within and outside of the province,

640
00:26:46,990 --> 00:26:48,520
only these were published.

641
00:26:50,420 --> 00:26:51,620
Gratifying results.

642
00:26:52,480 --> 00:26:54,080
What's gratifying about it?

643
00:26:54,090 --> 00:26:55,290
Not even half made it.

644
00:26:55,710 --> 00:26:57,170
Someone suppressed them.

645
00:27:00,440 --> 00:27:01,150
Did you see the new slogans

646
00:27:01,150 --> 00:27:02,110
in the county?

647
00:27:02,350 --> 00:27:03,350
Don't be anxious.

648
00:27:04,910 --> 00:27:05,910
I saw them.

649
00:27:09,660 --> 00:27:11,120
I really didn't expect it.

650
00:27:11,390 --> 00:27:12,370
It was Uncle Lin.

651
00:27:13,750 --> 00:27:14,830
He instructed the propaganda team

652
00:27:14,830 --> 00:27:15,310
to do it.

653
00:27:15,660 --> 00:27:16,740
You child,

654
00:27:16,960 --> 00:27:18,620
how can you say "instructed"?

655
00:27:19,050 --> 00:27:19,880
Propaganda and the economy

656
00:27:19,880 --> 00:27:21,480
are under his charge anyway.

657
00:27:21,750 --> 00:27:23,290
Lin is just doing his job.

658
00:27:24,400 --> 00:27:24,920
He did this,

659
00:27:24,920 --> 00:27:26,120
and I can understand.

660
00:27:26,500 --> 00:27:27,220
He genuinely wants

661
00:27:27,220 --> 00:27:28,750
what's best for the county.

662
00:27:29,770 --> 00:27:31,430
But he doesn't understand us.

663
00:27:31,510 --> 00:27:32,180
Alright.

664
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:36,320
The matter at hand

665
00:27:36,340 --> 00:27:37,800
is what's most important.

666
00:27:39,090 --> 00:27:39,940
In this development zone's

667
00:27:39,940 --> 00:27:40,680
report,

668
00:27:42,050 --> 00:27:42,790
it involves

669
00:27:42,880 --> 00:27:43,740
over twenty mining sites

670
00:27:43,740 --> 00:27:44,940
within Bolamula.

671
00:27:45,850 --> 00:27:46,640
If we really go ahead

672
00:27:46,640 --> 00:27:47,610
with this plan,

673
00:27:48,270 --> 00:27:49,000
how many people will have to enter

674
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:50,260
the Uninhabited Zone?

675
00:27:50,280 --> 00:27:52,940
Can it still be called
an Uninhabited Zone then?

676
00:27:53,600 --> 00:27:55,860
I've been studying this report for days.

677
00:27:56,200 --> 00:27:57,260
I've been trying to find

678
00:27:57,260 --> 00:27:57,690
a solution

679
00:27:57,690 --> 00:27:59,210
that satisfies everyone.

680
00:28:00,330 --> 00:28:01,330
Is that possible?

681
00:28:05,310 --> 00:28:06,930
[Request for Approval to Establish
the Mazhi Economic Development Zone]

682
00:28:05,750 --> 00:28:06,750
What do you think?

683
00:28:10,780 --> 00:28:11,980
It's a pipe dream.

684
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,620
How does the saying go?

685
00:28:18,160 --> 00:28:19,090
You can boil a stone for years,

686
00:28:19,090 --> 00:28:20,690
but it won't taste like meat.

687
00:28:21,310 --> 00:28:22,010
You can churn creek water,

688
00:28:22,010 --> 00:28:23,410
but you won't get butter.

689
00:28:24,970 --> 00:28:25,860
So what do we do?

690
00:28:26,260 --> 00:28:26,930
The county standing committee meeting

691
00:28:26,930 --> 00:28:28,170
is in three days.

692
00:28:28,810 --> 00:28:30,010
Your objections,

693
00:28:30,530 --> 00:28:32,330
will the committee accept them?

694
00:28:32,850 --> 00:28:33,640
Even if they don't,

695
00:28:33,640 --> 00:28:35,100
I still have to raise them.

696
00:28:35,960 --> 00:28:37,060
Whether Lin and the committee

697
00:28:37,060 --> 00:28:38,120
understand or not,

698
00:28:38,250 --> 00:28:39,910
this isn't a personal grudge.

699
00:28:40,310 --> 00:28:42,220
Since some people can't understand,

700
00:28:42,220 --> 00:28:43,820
we'll just have to find a way.

701
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:45,790
We've already come

702
00:28:45,790 --> 00:28:46,700
this far.

703
00:28:47,470 --> 00:28:48,670
We absolutely cannot

704
00:28:48,780 --> 00:28:49,900
follow the development zone's path

705
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:50,630
any further.

706
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:56,290
I haven't seen you all day.

707
00:28:56,410 --> 00:28:57,340
Where did you go?

708
00:28:59,600 --> 00:29:00,420
Post office.

709
00:29:00,840 --> 00:29:01,770
Speak properly.

710
00:29:02,930 --> 00:29:04,430
I got this from the post office.

711
00:29:04,430 --> 00:29:04,920
Look.

712
00:29:16,390 --> 00:29:20,150
[Invitation]

713
00:29:22,420 --> 00:29:23,500
This is an invitation

714
00:29:23,500 --> 00:29:24,560
sent from Beijing.

715
00:29:25,250 --> 00:29:26,180
Beijing Friends of Nature

716
00:29:26,180 --> 00:29:27,090
Environmental Protection Association,

717
00:29:27,090 --> 00:29:28,350
together with Peking University

718
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:29,670
and Beijing Forestry University,

719
00:29:29,670 --> 00:29:31,600
are inviting you to give a lecture.

720
00:29:33,330 --> 00:29:33,850
Really?

721
00:29:34,250 --> 00:29:35,210
A speech in Beijing?

722
00:29:35,210 --> 00:29:35,830
Look.

723
00:29:39,050 --> 00:29:39,660
Duo.

724
00:29:40,510 --> 00:29:41,670
They want you
to lecture university students.

725
00:29:41,670 --> 00:29:42,480
Can you do it?

726
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:44,110
No problem.

727
00:29:44,230 --> 00:29:45,090
Let me see. Let me see.

728
00:29:45,090 --> 00:29:45,960
Many university students

729
00:29:45,960 --> 00:29:46,980
couldn't come here

730
00:29:46,980 --> 00:29:47,590
to visit.

731
00:29:47,740 --> 00:29:48,850
But regarding the topic
of environmental protection,

732
00:29:48,850 --> 00:29:49,750
they care a lot.

733
00:29:50,080 --> 00:29:50,610
Last time,

734
00:29:50,610 --> 00:29:52,270
when I went back to the provincial capital
to file a report,

735
00:29:52,270 --> 00:29:53,590
I contacted a few alumni associations.

736
00:29:53,590 --> 00:29:56,220
The student representatives
were very enthusiastic.

737
00:29:56,220 --> 00:29:56,770
There were also a few

738
00:29:56,770 --> 00:29:58,250
environmental professors.

739
00:29:58,250 --> 00:29:58,640
They said

740
00:29:58,640 --> 00:29:59,440
they could give us

741
00:29:59,440 --> 00:30:00,500
academic support.

742
00:30:12,580 --> 00:30:14,190
If only He were still here.

743
00:30:20,170 --> 00:30:21,860
We could've gone together.

744
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:39,410
Name.

745
00:30:42,420 --> 00:30:43,380
Zhaba Jiangcuo.

746
00:30:43,940 --> 00:30:45,230
A name needs a surname.

747
00:30:45,830 --> 00:30:46,360
Chishao.

748
00:30:47,550 --> 00:30:48,410
It's a big clan.

749
00:30:48,490 --> 00:30:50,430
That was hundreds of years ago.

750
00:30:50,920 --> 00:30:52,120
What is your surname?

751
00:30:52,590 --> 00:30:53,720
My surname is Adou.

752
00:30:54,880 --> 00:30:55,940
That's not bad too.

753
00:30:58,010 --> 00:30:58,880
Date of birth.

754
00:31:01,230 --> 00:31:01,900
Autumn.

755
00:31:02,970 --> 00:31:03,830
What do you mean by autumn?

756
00:31:03,830 --> 00:31:05,560
You can't just write "Autumn."

757
00:31:05,720 --> 00:31:07,190
Mom said it was autumn.

758
00:31:09,940 --> 00:31:11,200
It needs to be precise.

759
00:31:11,570 --> 00:31:12,700
Like on your ID card.

760
00:31:13,170 --> 00:31:14,450
That's not accurate.

761
00:31:15,250 --> 00:31:16,850
That was noted

762
00:31:16,880 --> 00:31:18,350
when Mom was getting me an ID card

763
00:31:18,350 --> 00:31:19,070
in the county town.

764
00:31:19,070 --> 00:31:20,660
I was already 10 years old then.

765
00:31:20,660 --> 00:31:21,550
It has to be that one.

766
00:31:21,550 --> 00:31:23,410
Otherwise, they won't accept it.

767
00:31:24,500 --> 00:31:25,560
What a huge hassle.

768
00:31:26,260 --> 00:31:27,450
I'll go look for it.

769
00:31:34,880 --> 00:31:36,160
Height and blood type.

770
00:31:37,490 --> 00:31:38,250
I don't know.

771
00:31:39,290 --> 00:31:40,890
Just write the same as yours.

772
00:31:41,830 --> 00:31:42,440
Then I'll write

773
00:31:42,440 --> 00:31:43,660
2cm shorter than me.

774
00:31:45,240 --> 00:31:46,010
Did you get Mrs. Nima's

775
00:31:46,010 --> 00:31:47,290
air-dried beef?

776
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:48,560
I got it.

777
00:31:48,590 --> 00:31:50,160
She even gave us a cow leg.

778
00:31:51,410 --> 00:31:52,070
It's so big!

779
00:31:58,750 --> 00:31:59,810
That's quite a lot.

780
00:32:00,570 --> 00:32:01,510
I don't know if

781
00:32:01,670 --> 00:32:02,330
the Captain's suitcase

782
00:32:02,330 --> 00:32:03,400
can hold it all.

783
00:32:08,030 --> 00:32:08,720
Zhacuo,

784
00:32:09,300 --> 00:32:09,890
why are you letting someone else

785
00:32:09,890 --> 00:32:10,850
write for you?

786
00:32:10,900 --> 00:32:11,680
Didn't you say you already started

787
00:32:11,680 --> 00:32:13,410
learning Chinese characters?

788
00:32:13,460 --> 00:32:14,660
I can't write it well.

789
00:32:14,900 --> 00:32:16,830
The application form
for the Forestry Police

790
00:32:16,830 --> 00:32:17,890
cannot be altered.

791
00:32:19,500 --> 00:32:20,870
I'm afraid of making mistakes.

792
00:32:20,870 --> 00:32:22,050
You have to learn quickly.

793
00:32:22,050 --> 00:32:23,060
Otherwise, when you go to
the Provincial Public Security Department,

794
00:32:23,060 --> 00:32:24,610
you won't even pass the exam.

795
00:32:24,610 --> 00:32:25,550
No problem.

796
00:32:26,180 --> 00:32:26,770
Sangba says

797
00:32:26,770 --> 00:32:28,380
my Chinese character level

798
00:32:28,770 --> 00:32:29,520
has reached

799
00:32:29,550 --> 00:32:31,570
the fifth or sixth grade
of elementary school.

800
00:32:31,570 --> 00:32:32,150
Really?

801
00:32:32,500 --> 00:32:33,610
He's improved that fast?

802
00:32:33,610 --> 00:32:36,070
Maybe third, fourth, fifth,
or sixth grade.

803
00:32:36,680 --> 00:32:37,740
Hurry up and write.

804
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:39,720
If the application form is submitted late

805
00:32:39,720 --> 00:32:40,640
and you two can't wear police uniforms,

806
00:32:40,640 --> 00:32:41,570
don't blame me.

807
00:32:42,330 --> 00:32:43,000
Hurry up.

808
00:32:43,030 --> 00:32:44,030
Have you found it?

809
00:32:44,350 --> 00:32:45,480
I'm looking.

810
00:32:45,990 --> 00:32:46,760
Where is Han?

811
00:32:48,350 --> 00:32:49,460
He was just here.

812
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:50,620
Found it.

813
00:32:54,530 --> 00:32:56,180
It was chewed up by a rat.

814
00:32:56,210 --> 00:32:56,880
Let me see.

815
00:33:00,140 --> 00:33:02,270
You'd better get it reissued quickly.

816
00:33:02,380 --> 00:33:03,240
Write faster.

817
00:33:03,720 --> 00:33:04,260
Okay.

818
00:33:06,740 --> 00:33:08,000
Do I need to reissue it?

819
00:33:09,150 --> 00:33:10,180
Of course you do.

820
00:33:23,480 --> 00:33:24,080
Thanks.

821
00:33:31,350 --> 00:33:32,700
Since I came back last time,

822
00:33:32,700 --> 00:33:33,650
it keeps stalling.

823
00:33:33,650 --> 00:33:35,050
I can't find the problem.

824
00:33:35,110 --> 00:33:36,110
It must be too old.

825
00:33:39,080 --> 00:33:40,010
All these years,

826
00:33:40,670 --> 00:33:42,550
it's been driven too hard
in the mountains.

827
00:33:42,550 --> 00:33:43,810
It should be scrapped.

828
00:33:44,250 --> 00:33:44,750
If it doesn't go into the mountains

829
00:33:44,750 --> 00:33:46,000
and just runs on city roads,

830
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:47,090
it's still fine.

831
00:33:47,940 --> 00:33:49,290
If it doesn't go into the mountains,

832
00:33:49,290 --> 00:33:50,550
what do you need it for?

833
00:33:54,280 --> 00:33:55,080
Han,

834
00:33:55,170 --> 00:33:56,260
about your situation,

835
00:33:56,260 --> 00:33:57,720
I've applied to the Chief.

836
00:33:58,300 --> 00:33:58,750
He is currently

837
00:33:58,750 --> 00:34:01,530
submitting a report
to the Provincial Forestry Police.

838
00:34:01,530 --> 00:34:02,480
Even if you can't get

839
00:34:02,480 --> 00:34:03,420
a permanent position
in the police force...

840
00:34:03,420 --> 00:34:04,220
Please don't.

841
00:34:05,140 --> 00:34:06,160
There's no need to make things difficult

842
00:34:06,160 --> 00:34:07,480
for the leaders because of me,

843
00:34:07,480 --> 00:34:09,040
a person with a criminal record.

844
00:34:09,040 --> 00:34:10,900
I've already thought it through.

845
00:34:11,210 --> 00:34:12,980
Once the reserve is established

846
00:34:12,980 --> 00:34:14,420
and the Forestry Police are in place,

847
00:34:14,420 --> 00:34:16,080
it will be time for me to leave.

848
00:34:17,100 --> 00:34:18,100
Where will you go?

849
00:34:18,929 --> 00:34:20,790
I haven't thought about that yet.

850
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:23,300
This old buddy

851
00:34:24,909 --> 00:34:26,280
can still run

852
00:34:26,300 --> 00:34:27,400
on the city roads,

853
00:34:28,730 --> 00:34:29,440
right?

854
00:34:30,880 --> 00:34:31,780
If you leave,

855
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:33,030
fixing these junk cars

856
00:34:33,030 --> 00:34:34,380
will fall on me alone.

857
00:34:35,070 --> 00:34:36,239
If you dare to leave,

858
00:34:36,659 --> 00:34:38,590
I'll arrest you and bring you back.

859
00:34:40,210 --> 00:34:40,780
That sounds like

860
00:34:40,780 --> 00:34:42,639
something a deputy captain would say.

861
00:34:42,639 --> 00:34:44,429
I'll be waiting for you to arrest me.

862
00:34:44,429 --> 00:34:45,520
You really are...

863
00:34:47,030 --> 00:34:48,280
Although I made

864
00:34:48,380 --> 00:34:49,580
mistakes in the past,

865
00:34:50,230 --> 00:34:50,810
I still have the right

866
00:34:50,810 --> 00:34:52,139
to choose now, don't I?

867
00:34:56,210 --> 00:34:57,230
When I leave,

868
00:34:58,290 --> 00:35:00,150
get some good liquor ready for me.

869
00:35:00,610 --> 00:35:01,470
Shao mentioned

870
00:35:02,500 --> 00:35:04,050
a foreign liquor before.

871
00:35:05,150 --> 00:35:06,730
Called Whis...

872
00:35:07,510 --> 00:35:08,550
Whis... what was it again?

873
00:35:08,550 --> 00:35:10,030
That's not your choice.

874
00:35:11,900 --> 00:35:13,020
What are you doing?

875
00:35:13,920 --> 00:35:15,450
Trying to be an unsung hero?

876
00:35:15,710 --> 00:35:16,770
Don't give me that.

877
00:35:17,610 --> 00:35:18,510
A proper job

878
00:35:18,530 --> 00:35:19,540
is what you deserve to get.

879
00:35:19,540 --> 00:35:20,230
If you can't be in Public Security,

880
00:35:20,230 --> 00:35:21,510
then be a ranger.

881
00:35:22,070 --> 00:35:22,880
The establishment of the reserve

882
00:35:22,880 --> 00:35:24,280
relies on every one of us.

883
00:35:25,110 --> 00:35:25,670
Once established,

884
00:35:25,670 --> 00:35:26,960
it's not mission accomplished.

885
00:35:26,960 --> 00:35:28,360
It's just the beginning.

886
00:35:29,860 --> 00:35:31,260
In the future, this place

887
00:35:31,280 --> 00:35:33,410
will especially need people like you.

888
00:35:33,690 --> 00:35:34,280
Me?

889
00:35:37,560 --> 00:35:38,890
What kind of person am I?

890
00:35:41,510 --> 00:35:42,380
Stubborn.

891
00:35:43,250 --> 00:35:44,050
Someone who sticks to one thing

892
00:35:44,050 --> 00:35:45,180
and sees it through.

893
00:35:51,340 --> 00:35:52,340
I'm stubborn too.

894
00:35:53,170 --> 00:35:55,700
Stubborn people
understand each other best.

895
00:35:56,150 --> 00:35:57,280
Stubborn people...

896
00:36:03,830 --> 00:36:05,630
You can't tell from the outside.

897
00:36:05,890 --> 00:36:07,220
But when I part the hair,

898
00:36:07,480 --> 00:36:08,940
they're all white inside.

899
00:36:10,460 --> 00:36:11,920
You just figured that out?

900
00:36:14,730 --> 00:36:15,350
I still think

901
00:36:15,350 --> 00:36:16,720
you're like a young man.

902
00:36:19,630 --> 00:36:21,630
How did we get old without noticing?

903
00:36:23,270 --> 00:36:24,660
We've been together

904
00:36:25,540 --> 00:36:27,070
for almost half a lifetime.

905
00:36:31,680 --> 00:36:33,610
How long will you be gone this time?

906
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:36,660
Originally about ten days.

907
00:36:37,550 --> 00:36:38,880
Now it's hard to say.

908
00:36:39,760 --> 00:36:41,490
There are university lectures

909
00:36:41,500 --> 00:36:42,300
and speeches.

910
00:36:43,280 --> 00:36:43,960
Shao said

911
00:36:44,030 --> 00:36:44,610
there are some companies

912
00:36:44,610 --> 00:36:45,840
that want to donate to us

913
00:36:45,840 --> 00:36:46,840
waiting to see me.

914
00:36:48,360 --> 00:36:49,880
I also need to visit

915
00:36:50,140 --> 00:36:51,430
the National Environmental
Protection Bureau

916
00:36:51,430 --> 00:36:53,230
and leaders from the Ministry of Forestry.

917
00:36:53,230 --> 00:36:53,940
To report to them

918
00:36:53,940 --> 00:36:55,050
on our work here.

919
00:36:55,580 --> 00:36:57,020
The reserve's establishment

920
00:36:57,020 --> 00:36:58,480
depends on their support.

921
00:37:00,980 --> 00:37:02,340
I'll pray for you all.

922
00:37:02,780 --> 00:37:03,760
I have a feeling.

923
00:37:04,640 --> 00:37:05,960
Your good days

924
00:37:06,050 --> 00:37:06,920
are coming.

925
00:37:10,190 --> 00:37:11,890
When the reserve is established,

926
00:37:11,890 --> 00:37:13,620
the team will have more people.

927
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:14,800
I can then stay home

928
00:37:14,800 --> 00:37:16,400
and spend more time with you.

929
00:37:16,910 --> 00:37:17,330
Then,

930
00:37:17,360 --> 00:37:19,020
we'll go traveling together.

931
00:37:19,190 --> 00:37:20,280
We'll go to big cities

932
00:37:20,280 --> 00:37:21,410
and look around too.

933
00:37:22,180 --> 00:37:23,240
What about our son?

934
00:37:24,800 --> 00:37:26,590
He even dares to go
to the Uninhabited Zone.

935
00:37:26,590 --> 00:37:28,190
What's there to worry about?

936
00:37:28,440 --> 00:37:29,640
Just let him stay home

937
00:37:29,930 --> 00:37:31,260
and look after himself.

938
00:37:33,820 --> 00:37:34,500
Dad.

939
00:37:35,540 --> 00:37:37,400
Why are you bragging to Mom again?

940
00:37:40,380 --> 00:37:41,780
What are you laughing at?

941
00:37:41,900 --> 00:37:42,320
When the time comes,

942
00:37:42,320 --> 00:37:42,980
your mom and I

943
00:37:42,980 --> 00:37:44,230
will go traveling by ourselves.

944
00:37:44,230 --> 00:37:44,980
We'll leave you

945
00:37:44,980 --> 00:37:45,530
at home all alone.

946
00:37:45,530 --> 00:37:47,590
Let's see if you can still smile then.

947
00:37:47,900 --> 00:37:49,760
Dad, this hairstyle looks great.

948
00:37:50,480 --> 00:37:52,650
You should wear it like this from now on.

949
00:37:52,650 --> 00:37:53,280
I used to be

950
00:37:53,300 --> 00:37:54,700
handsome back in the day.

951
00:37:54,710 --> 00:37:55,130
Otherwise,

952
00:37:55,130 --> 00:37:57,260
how could I be good enough for your mom?

953
00:37:57,840 --> 00:37:59,130
Now, in our family,

954
00:37:59,400 --> 00:38:00,460
the most handsome one

955
00:38:00,460 --> 00:38:01,750
is Tashi.

956
00:38:04,490 --> 00:38:04,770
Dad,

957
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:05,760
are you going to this university

958
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:06,760
to give a lecture?

959
00:38:07,510 --> 00:38:08,970
It's not really a lecture.

960
00:38:09,230 --> 00:38:10,690
I'm just going to tell them

961
00:38:10,730 --> 00:38:12,790
about what the Mountain Patrol does.

962
00:38:13,050 --> 00:38:13,780
Tashi,

963
00:38:14,420 --> 00:38:15,400
tell dad what gift

964
00:38:15,400 --> 00:38:16,260
you want.

965
00:38:16,530 --> 00:38:18,010
He'll bring it back for you.

966
00:38:18,010 --> 00:38:20,070
I don't need him to bring me anything.

967
00:38:20,160 --> 00:38:21,950
I'm going to get into a university
in Beijing.

968
00:38:21,950 --> 00:38:23,510
I'll go to Peking University.

969
00:38:23,510 --> 00:38:24,030
If I want something,

970
00:38:24,030 --> 00:38:25,090
I'll buy it myself.

971
00:38:25,300 --> 00:38:26,170
Okay.

972
00:38:27,500 --> 00:38:28,460
A fifteen-year-old man

973
00:38:28,460 --> 00:38:29,800
makes his own decisions.

974
00:38:29,800 --> 00:38:30,780
A fifteen-year-old girl

975
00:38:30,780 --> 00:38:32,070
grinds her own tsampa.

976
00:38:33,440 --> 00:38:34,760
Our little Tashi

977
00:38:34,920 --> 00:38:35,880
has grown up.

978
00:38:37,340 --> 00:38:38,170
From now on,

979
00:38:38,220 --> 00:38:40,880
there's another decision-maker
in the family.

980
00:38:45,860 --> 00:38:46,720
This is for you.

981
00:38:49,210 --> 00:38:50,000
What is it?

982
00:38:51,730 --> 00:38:52,570
Safe travels.

983
00:39:32,590 --> 00:39:33,300
Ms. Kang.

984
00:39:48,060 --> 00:39:48,730
Sorry to disturb you,

985
00:39:48,730 --> 00:39:49,660
Director Zhang.

986
00:39:53,050 --> 00:39:54,580
You finally agreed to come.

987
00:39:57,550 --> 00:39:58,880
It's been so many years.

988
00:39:59,860 --> 00:40:01,390
This tree has grown taller.

989
00:40:03,460 --> 00:40:04,610
The bed is made.

990
00:40:06,340 --> 00:40:07,880
Mom, you're back.

991
00:40:08,630 --> 00:40:09,160
The Captain is staying with us

992
00:40:09,160 --> 00:40:09,960
for the night.

993
00:40:10,050 --> 00:40:11,800
He's heading straight to Beijing tomorrow.

994
00:40:11,800 --> 00:40:12,670
Okay, okay.

995
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:13,660
You're the boss.

996
00:40:14,350 --> 00:40:14,870
Come on.

997
00:40:15,540 --> 00:40:16,470
Come help me out.

998
00:40:16,930 --> 00:40:18,520
We'll cook a sheep's head today.

999
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:20,070
That's too much trouble, Director Zhang.

1000
00:40:20,070 --> 00:40:21,300
Just make something simple.

1001
00:40:21,300 --> 00:40:22,340
Just sit tight.

1002
00:40:22,450 --> 00:40:23,450
Wait for the food.

1003
00:40:48,780 --> 00:40:50,180
What are you laughing at?

1004
00:40:52,860 --> 00:40:53,400
I was thinking about

1005
00:40:53,400 --> 00:40:54,800
when you first came here.

1006
00:40:57,220 --> 00:40:59,350
How was my mom like
when she first came?

1007
00:41:00,890 --> 00:41:02,020
I wouldn't dare say.

1008
00:41:02,570 --> 00:41:03,500
Tell me, tell me!

1009
00:41:03,670 --> 00:41:04,600
How was she like?

1010
00:41:05,400 --> 00:41:06,900
I know what he wants to say.

1011
00:41:08,210 --> 00:41:08,650
Back then,

1012
00:41:08,650 --> 00:41:09,710
I had just arrived from Nanjing

1013
00:41:09,710 --> 00:41:10,910
and wasn't used to it.

1014
00:41:10,940 --> 00:41:11,480
In this place,

1015
00:41:11,480 --> 00:41:13,930
there was only highland barley,
beef, and mutton.

1016
00:41:13,930 --> 00:41:14,860
I got so sick of it

1017
00:41:15,150 --> 00:41:17,010
so I pestered the local officials

1018
00:41:17,050 --> 00:41:18,030
for vegetables.

1019
00:41:19,270 --> 00:41:20,530
She made quite a scene.

1020
00:41:21,020 --> 00:41:23,150
She'd cry if she didn't get to eat them.

1021
00:41:25,690 --> 00:41:26,460
It worried our

1022
00:41:26,460 --> 00:41:28,790
County Party Secretary so much back then.

1023
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:29,880
Later, the county

1024
00:41:29,880 --> 00:41:31,080
went to great lengths

1025
00:41:31,330 --> 00:41:33,940
to bring a truckload of vegetables
from Tianduo.

1026
00:41:33,940 --> 00:41:35,600
But the journey took too long.

1027
00:41:36,530 --> 00:41:37,400
By the time they got to Mazhi,

1028
00:41:37,400 --> 00:41:38,660
the vegetables were frozen.

1029
00:41:38,660 --> 00:41:40,660
They tasted bitter when we ate them.

1030
00:41:40,880 --> 00:41:42,210
That made her cry again.

1031
00:41:43,810 --> 00:41:44,590
Was my mom such a crybaby

1032
00:41:44,590 --> 00:41:45,650
when she was young?

1033
00:41:46,810 --> 00:41:47,580
She sure was.

1034
00:41:49,610 --> 00:41:50,650
But your mom,

1035
00:41:51,360 --> 00:41:52,590
apart from loving food,

1036
00:41:52,590 --> 00:41:53,720
had no other faults.

1037
00:41:55,510 --> 00:41:56,120
Back then,

1038
00:41:56,150 --> 00:41:57,210
she slept in a tent.

1039
00:41:57,770 --> 00:41:59,700
She rode a horse to make her rounds.

1040
00:42:00,270 --> 00:42:01,870
She even bathed in the river.

1041
00:42:02,050 --> 00:42:02,840
How do you know

1042
00:42:02,840 --> 00:42:03,650
that I bathed in the river?

1043
00:42:03,650 --> 00:42:04,070
Yeah.

1044
00:42:04,120 --> 00:42:04,980
How do you know?

1045
00:42:05,360 --> 00:42:06,820
It was all over the county.

1046
00:42:07,760 --> 00:42:08,370
Anyway, she was tougher

1047
00:42:08,370 --> 00:42:09,440
than the men.

1048
00:42:10,380 --> 00:42:10,780
Otherwise,

1049
00:42:10,780 --> 00:42:12,420
with so many doctors in the county,

1050
00:42:12,420 --> 00:42:13,610
why would everyone only call her

1051
00:42:13,610 --> 00:42:14,360
Ms. Kang?

1052
00:42:16,340 --> 00:42:17,280
Back then, in the pastoral areas,

1053
00:42:17,280 --> 00:42:18,940
echinococcosis was rampant.

1054
00:42:20,320 --> 00:42:21,800
She mobilized the county

1055
00:42:22,220 --> 00:42:23,360
to make a batch of solar cookers

1056
00:42:23,360 --> 00:42:24,560
and distribute them.

1057
00:42:24,730 --> 00:42:26,790
She promoted drinking boiled water.

1058
00:42:27,800 --> 00:42:28,730
Now she's working on

1059
00:42:28,730 --> 00:42:30,860
a plan for women's sanitary products.

1060
00:42:32,570 --> 00:42:34,430
Your mom dedicated her whole life

1061
00:42:34,570 --> 00:42:35,780
to the pastoral area,

1062
00:42:36,260 --> 00:42:37,360
to the grasslands.

1063
00:42:39,840 --> 00:42:41,640
Compared to her contributions,

1064
00:42:42,460 --> 00:42:43,890
the work we do

1065
00:42:43,940 --> 00:42:44,920
is nothing.

1066
00:42:48,820 --> 00:42:49,320
It's useless to say

1067
00:42:49,320 --> 00:42:50,550
pretty words here.

1068
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:53,260
If you're so capable,
go say them in Beijing.

1069
00:42:57,320 --> 00:42:58,580
Why aren't you eating?

1070
00:42:58,930 --> 00:42:59,930
Is my cooking bad?

1071
00:42:59,930 --> 00:43:01,460
It's good. It's delicious.

1072
00:43:02,540 --> 00:43:03,540
It looks delicious.
